FT  01 MAR 93 / People: The Weir Group
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The family ties which have bound the descendants of <PERSON>George</PERSON> and <PERSON>James Weir</PERSON> to
<LOCATION>Scotland</LOCATION>'s biggest and most successful engineering company for more than a
century are slowly unravelling. <PERSON>George Weir</PERSON>, a 52-year-old great grandson,
has retired after 20 years on <ORGANIZATION>The Weir Group</ORGANIZATION> board, leaving his brother,
<PERSON>Viscount Weir</PERSON>, 59, as the sole remaining member of the family involved in
the business. <PERSON>Viscount Weir</PERSON> has been chairman since <DATE>1972</DATE>, apart from a brief
gap in the early <DATE>1980s</DATE> when the company ran into financial problems and <ORGANIZATION>Lord
Tombs</ORGANIZATION> took the chair.
